The paper discusses the use of robotic manipulators and visual environment sensors, which are commonly used in the field of robotics (cs.RO). The method presented involves 3D camera-based workspace mapping, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also mentions the use of predictive and reflexive robot manipulator trajectory estimation, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the goal of the work is to make the operation more flexible in unstructured dynamic workspaces, which involves control systems (cs.SY).
